https://the-decoder.com/?p=33314", "https://www.technologyreview.com/?p=1133848"], "today_date": "2026-03-25", "today_news": [{"id": "https://the-decoder.com/?p=33576", "title": "ChatGPT is turning into a shopping platform with product images, prices, and comparisons, but no checkout", "summary": "ChatGPT is getting visual shopping features that show products with images, prices, and side-by-side comparisons right in the chat. At the same time, OpenAI is dropping its own payment system and handing checkout off to retailers.", "link": "https://the-decoder.com/chatgpt-is-turning-into-a-shopping-platform-with-product-images-prices-and-comparisons-but-no-checkout/", "source": "The Decoder", "image": null, "score": 7}, {"id": "https://www.technologyreview.com/?p=1134540", "title": "The Download: tracing AI-fueled delusions, and OpenAI admits Microsoft risks", "summary": "This is today&#8217;s edition of The Download, our weekday newsletter that provides a daily dose of what&#8217;s going on in the world of technology. The hardest question to answer about AI-fueled&#160;delusions&#160; What&#160;actually happens&#160;when people spiral into delusion with AI? To find ...", "link": "https://www.technologyreview.com/2026/03/24/1134540/the-download-tracing-ai-fueled-delusions-openai-warns-microsoft-risks/", "source": "MIT Tech Review", "image": null, "score": 5}, {"id": "https://the-decoder.com/?p=33592", "title": "Popular AI proxy LiteLLM got hacked with malware that spreads through Kubernetes clusters", "summary": "LiteLLM, a popular open-source proxy for AI APIs, has been compromised with malware that steals credentials and spreads across cloud systems. NVIDIA AI Director Jim Fan warns this represents a new class of attacks targeting AI agents.", "link": "https://the-decoder.com/popular-ai-proxy-litellm-got-hacked-with-malware-that-spreads-through-kubernetes-clusters/", "source": "The Decoder", "image": null, "score": 5}, {"id": "https://the-decoder.com/?p=33587", "title": "Google Deepmind's Gemini 3.1 Flash-Lite generates websites almost in real time", "summary": "Google shows in a demo how Gemini 3.1 Flash-Lite generates complete websites in real time. Fast, cheap - but also useful?", "link": "https://the-decoder.com/google-deepminds-gemini-3-1-flash-lite-generates-websites-almost-in-real-time/", "source": "The Decoder", "image": null, "score": 4}, {"id": "https://the-decoder.com/?p=33573", "title": "Microsoft snaps up Texas data center that Oracle and OpenAI left behind", "summary": "Microsoft has agreed to lease a data center in Abilene, Texas, that was originally built for Oracle and OpenAI, Bloomberg News reports.", "link": "https://the-decoder.com/microsoft-snaps-up-texas-data-center-that-oracle-and-openai-left-behind/", "source": "The Decoder", "image": null, "score": 4}, {"id": "https://www.technologyreview.com/?p=1134531", "title": "Exclusive eBook: Are we ready to hand AI agents the keys?", "summary": "We\u2019re starting to give AI agents real autonomy, but are we prepared for what could happen next? This subscriber-only eBook explores this and angles from experts, such as \u201cIf we continue on the current path \u2026 we are basically playing Russian roulette with humanity.\u201d by Grace Huckins June 12, 2025 Rel...", "link": "https://www.technologyreview.com/2026/03/24/1134531/exclusive-ebook-are-we-ready-to-hand-ai-agents-the-keys/", "source": "MIT Tech Review", "image": null, "score": 2}, {"id": "https://www.technologyreview.com/?p=1134562", "title": "This scientist rewarmed and studied pieces of his friend\u2019s cryopreserved brain", "summary": "L. Stephen Coles\u2019s brain sits cushioned in a vat at a storage facility in Arizona. It has been held there at a temperature of around \u2212146 degrees \u00b0C for over a decade, largely undisturbed. That is, apart from the time, a little over a year ago, when scientists slowly lifted the brain to take photos&...", "link": "https://www.technologyreview.com/2026/03/24/1134562/cryopreservation-brain-cryonics-organ-transplantation/", "source": "MIT Tech Review", "image": null, "score": 2}, {"id": "https://the-decoder.com/?p=33583", "title": "A man created thousands of fake accounts to stream AI songs billions of times and pocket $8 million in royalties", "summary": "AI songs, fake accounts, billions of bot plays: a North Carolina man has pleaded guilty to scamming streaming platforms out of more than eight million dollars.", "link": "https://the-decoder.com/a-man-created-thousands-of-fake-accounts-to-stream-ai-songs-billions-of-times-and-pocket-8-million-in-royalties/", "source": "The Decoder", "image": null, "score": 0}], "today_tech": [{"id": "oai:arXiv.org:2603.23057v1", "title": "Prompt Amplification and Zero-Shot Late Fusion in Audio-Language Models for Speech Emotion Recognition", "summary": "Abstract: Audio-Language Models (ALMs) are making strides in understanding speech and non-speech audio. However, domain-specialist Foundation Models (FMs) remain the best for closed-ended speech processing tasks such as Speech Emotion Recognition (SER). Using ALMs for Zero-shot SER is a popular choi...", "link": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.23057", "source": "arXiv Audio & Speech", "image": "https://arxiv.org/html/2603.23057v1/2603.23057v1/figures/zeroshotfusion.png", "score": 18}, {"id": "oai:arXiv.org:2603.22293v1", "title": "TIPS: Turn-Level Information-Potential Reward Shaping for Search-Augmented LLMs", "summary": "Abstract: Search-augmented large language models (LLMs) trained with reinforcement learning (RL) have achieved strong results on open-domain question answering (QA), but training still remains a significant challenge. The optimization is often unstable due to sparse rewards and difficult credit assi...", "link": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.22293", "source": "arXiv NLP", "image": "https://arxiv.org/html/2603.22293v1/2603.22293v1/x1.png", "score": 14}, {"id": "oai:arXiv.org:2603.22321v1", "title": "From Instructions to Assistance: a Dataset Aligning Instruction Manuals with Assembly Videos for Evaluating Multimodal LLMs", "summary": "Abstract: The recent advancements introduced by Large Language Models (LLMs) have transformed how Artificial Intelligence (AI) can support complex, real world tasks, pushing research outside the text boundaries towards multi modal contexts and leading to Multimodal Large Language Models (MLMs). Give...", "link": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.22321", "source": "arXiv CV", "image": "https://arxiv.org/html/2603.22321v1/2603.22321v1/x1.png", "score": 14}, {"id": "oai:arXiv.org:2603.22287v1", "title": "Founder effects shape the evolutionary dynamics of multimodality in open LLM families", "summary": "Abstract: Large language model (LLM) families are improving rapidly, yet it remains unclear how quickly multimodal capabilities emerge and propagate within open families. Using the ModelBiome AI Ecosystem dataset of Hugging Face model metadata and recorded lineage fields (>1.8x10^6 model entries), w...", "link": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.22287", "source": "arXiv CV", "image": "https://arxiv.org/html/2603.22287v1/2603.22287v1/fig1.png", "score": 13}, {"id": "oai:arXiv.org:2603.22288v1", "title": "Evaluating Prompting Strategies for Chart Question Answering with Large Language Models", "summary": "Abstract: Prompting strategies affect LLM reasoning performance, but their role in chart-based QA remains underexplored. We present a systematic evaluation of four widely used prompting paradigms (Zero-Shot, Few-Shot, Zero-Shot Chain-of-Thought, and Few-Shot Chain-of-Thought) across GPT-3.5, GPT-4, ...", "link": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.22288", "source": "arXiv NLP", "image": "https://arxiv.org/html/2603.22288v1/2603.22288v1/system_pipeline.png", "score": 12}]}